This paper deals with the problem of image recovery using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on the robustness of the image recovery process, which involves analyzing uncertainty and potential artifacts in the generated images. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which often deal with uncertainty and probabilistic models. Additionally, the paper uses MRI images as a dataset, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also explores the impact of different loss functions on the model's performance, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
